# FCM Web Push — Setup Patterns

## Problem 1 — Foreground listener misses messages on first page load

`onMessage` (Firebase foreground handler) requires an **active, controlling service worker**.
On the very first load the SW is still installing, so `onMessage` registers against an uncontrolled page and silently drops all messages. After a page refresh the SW is already active and everything works.

**Fix:** Make `subscribeForegroundMessages` async and await `serviceWorker.ready` before calling `onMessage`. Also sequence the calls in `FcmProvider` so the listener is only wired **after** `registerFcmToken()` resolves (which already awaits `serviceWorker.ready` internally).

```ts
// fcm.ts
export async function subscribeForegroundMessages(
  queryClient: QueryClient,
  onNotification: (n: ForegroundNotification) => void
): Promise<() => void> {
  const messaging = getFirebaseMessaging();
  if (!messaging) return () => {};

  if ("serviceWorker" in navigator) {
    await navigator.serviceWorker.ready; // ← wait for active SW
  }

  return onMessage(messaging, (payload) => { ... });
}
```

```ts
// FcmProvider.tsx — sequence: register first, then subscribe
registerFcmToken().then(() => {
  subscribeForegroundMessages(queryClient, handler).then((unsub) => { ... });
});
```

