## Problem 2 — Notification bell badge stale until page refresh

`onMessage` only fires when the tab is **visible**. When the tab is in the background the SW handles the FCM message directly, `onMessage` never fires, and `invalidateQueries` is never called — so the bell count stays stale until the user manually refreshes.

**Fix:** Add a `visibilitychange` listener in `FcmProvider` that invalidates the notifications query whenever the tab becomes visible. This covers background FCM, SW-delivered notifications, and any other server-side updates.

```ts
// FcmProvider.tsx
const handleVisibilityChange = () => {
  if (document.visibilityState === "visible") {
    queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ["notifications"] });
  }
};
document.addEventListener("visibilitychange", handleVisibilityChange);
// clean up in useEffect return
```

