## Problem 3 — Token cached, backend never re-called, topic subscription lost

`localStorage` caching skips the backend `/api/fcm-token` call on subsequent loads. If the backend subscribes the token to a topic (e.g. `all`) during that call, skipping it means the token is never (re-)subscribed and topic broadcasts are silently dropped.

**Fix:** Use `sessionStorage` as the "synced this session" guard. `localStorage` still caches the raw token to avoid unnecessary Firebase `getToken` round-trips, but the backend is called at least once per browser session.

```ts
const cached = localStorage.getItem(CACHED_TOKEN_KEY);
const syncedThisSession = sessionStorage.getItem(SESSION_SYNCED_KEY) === token;

if (cached === token && syncedThisSession) return; // skip only if both match

await ApiService.post("/api/fcm-token", { auth: true, body: { token, platform: "web" } });
localStorage.setItem(CACHED_TOKEN_KEY, token);
sessionStorage.setItem(SESSION_SYNCED_KEY, token);
```

Clear the session key on unregister so a fresh login always re-syncs:
```ts
sessionStorage.removeItem(SESSION_SYNCED_KEY);
```
